<F P=101> IRAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Besharati Discusses Joint Antidrug Campaign With Russian </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Besharati Discusses Joint Antidrug Campaign With Russian </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Envoy 

<F P=102>   LD0805191094 Tehran IRNA in English 1832 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0805191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 8, IRNA -- Russian Ambassador to Tehran 
Serguei [name as received] here Sunday suggested that Tehran and 
Moscow ink a memorandum of understanding on the anti-drugs 
campaign. 
  Tretyakov, in his meeting with Interior Minister 'Ali 
Mohammed Besharati, expressed hope that grounds would be paved 
for bilateral especially in the campaign against traffickers. 
[sentence as received] 
  He added that exchange of visits as well as sharing of 
experience and views by Iranian and Russian officials would help 
strengthen bilateral relations. 
  Besharati in return said Russia can play a "positive" role 
in 
solving regional disputes. 
  He expressed satisfaction with the two countries political 
and economic relations and called for their consolidation and 
deepening. 
  The Iranian official hailed the importance of Irano-Russian 
"historical" ties. 
  Besharati urged Russia to deal more actively with regional 
issues and said Russia as a permanent member of the United 
Nations Security Council can play an "important and effective" 
role on international scenes. 

</TEXT>

