<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Arrest Israeli, Seize Cocaine, Lab Equipment in </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Arrest Israeli, Seize Cocaine, Lab Equipment in </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Johannesburg 

<F P=102>   MB0905204294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1904 GMT 09 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0905204294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg May 9 SAPA -- A tip-off led 
Johannesburg narcotics policemen to a cocaine laboratory at an 
hotel in nearby Randburg on Saturday evening where they arrested 
an Israeli man and seized 1.5kg of the drug, valued at 
r[Rand]375,000. An airline ticket to Rio de Janeiro and foreign 
and local currency with a value of r60,000 were also found in a 
room at the city lodge, police reported on Monday. Laboratory 
equipment and chemicals were seized. 
  Mr Gazit Yechaim of Tel Aviv appeared in the Johannesburg 
magistrate's court on Monday and was remanded to wednesday. 

</TEXT>

