<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> TOGO </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Agency Sponsors Drug Enforcement Agent Training </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Agency Sponsors Drug Enforcement Agent Training </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB3004191094 Lome Radio Lome in French 1900 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB3004191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A three-week training workshop on drug abuse and 
trafficking ended this morning. The workshop was organized on 5 
April by the Togolese minister for territorial administration 
and security, with technical assistance from the UN Program for 
International Drug Control [UNPIDC]. It was conducted by the 
National Drug Laboratory. Here with the details is Gbode 
Elekonawo: 
  [Elekonawo) The training seminar was attended by about 20 
Togolese security force agents, who were initiated in various 
techniques for identifying illicit drugs. According to the 
organizers, drug enforcement agents often have problems 
identifying the many different kinds of drugs. That is why, as 
part of this assistance project to fight against drug 
trafficking and abuse, the UNPIDC donated identification kits to 
the gendarmerie and the police. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

