<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Garzon Explains Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Garzon Explains Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905122594 Madrid Teletexto TVE in Spanish 1000 GMT 9 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid Teletexto TVE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baltasar Garzon has told a news conference why he 
tendered his irrevocable resignation as secretary of state for 
the national plan on drugs. 
  Justice and Interior Minister [Juan Alberto] Belloch did not 
agree to his request for additional powers to combat drugs, and 
that is why Garzon decided to resign. 
  At his news conference, he also announced that he is 
resigning his seat as a deputy. In the last elections Garzon 
ran on the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party list in number two 
position, after Felipe Gonzalez. 

</TEXT>

