<H3> <TI>   Synthetic Drug Laboratory in St. Petersburg Raided </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Synthetic Drug Laboratory in St. Petersburg Raided </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305045094 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1000 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305045094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Video report by M. Velikoselskiy; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg remains the Russian leader in the 
illegal production of synthetic narcotics. Another underground 
laboratory was eliminated here a few days ago. A promising 
chemist and a capable manager combined their skills and prepared 
for sale a very rare and extremely effective drug. Its value on 
the narcotics market exceeds four billion rubles, and the number 
of single portions produced may be over a million. The state 
has confiscated from those arrested a large quantity of chemical 
reagents, laboratory equipment, and notes describing an original 
procedure for synthesizing narcotics, which the authors do not 
want to patent for the time being. [Video shows masked men in 
combat gear holding group of men at gunpoint; dogs; personnel 
examining packets of white powder, vials of liquid; production 
equipment; and men being searched] 

</TEXT>

