<H3> <TI>   Government Reaches Agreement With Labor Federation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Reaches Agreement With Labor Federation </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Further on Government, Coca Growers Agreement </H4>

<F P=102> PY0505225894 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 
1700 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0505225894 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Television Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After several weeks of negotiations, the government 
and coca growers have finally reached an agreement. 
  According to coca grower leaders, 80 percent of their 
demands 
will be honored with the signature of the agreements at dawn 
today. It is hoped, however, that these agreements will indeed 
be put into practice. 
  The negotiations with the government have resulted in one 
decree and two ministry resolutions. The decree establishes the 
equal participation of coca growers in the National Development 
Fund, Fonaral. One of the resolutions provides for the 
compulsory eradication only of new plantations; the second 
resolution, to be implemented immediately, provides for the open 
marketing and industrialization of coca leaf. The peasants, in 
exchange, have agreed to lift the road blockades. [recorded 
passage indistinct] 
  This morning the coca grower leaders travelled to El Chapare 
and the coca production areas to announce the agreement reached 
with the government and to suspend the pressure tactics, such as 
road blockades, adopted by the peasants. 

</TEXT>

