<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Narcotics Roundup for 6-11 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Narcotics Roundup for 6-11 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205041094 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205041094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
fileworthy reports from 6-11 May on counternarcotics operations 
in countries monitored by FBIS London Bureau. Sources are given 
in parentheses at the end of each report. 
<H5>  Italy </H5>
  An antidrug operation which began two days ago ended on 11 
May with the arrest of 13 people. Police from the Rome III 
group seized 6.5 kgs of cocaine valued at 4 billion lire. Among 
those arrested are high-profile criminal figures from Rome, 
Palermo Catania, and Calabria in southern Italy. The gang had 
its operational bases in the towns of Anzio and Ciampino, on the 
outskirts of Rome. (Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0727 
GMT 11 May 94) 
<H5>  Poland </H5>
  Former Costa Rican Ambassador to Poland Carlos Vargas Solis 
was charged by the prosecutor's office with smuggling 12.2 kg of 
heroin into Poland in April 1993. An indictment has been sent 
to the Provincial Court in Warsaw. On 20 April 1993 the Border 
Guard and customs officers at Warsaw's Okecie airport found 12.2 
kg of heroin in Solis' luggage. The luggage arrived from Delhi 
via Moscow. Solis arrived from Delhi on an earlier plane. 
(Warsaw PAP in Polish 1126 GMT 5 May 94) 
<H5>  Russia </H5>
  Sources in law enforcement bodies said a Moscow resident and 
an Afghan citizen were detained trying to sell 370 grams of 
heroin with a street value 172 million rubles. Investigations 
are being conducted. (Moscow INTERFAX in English 1610 GMT 6 May 
94) 
<H5>  Spain </H5>
  Police have arrested 32 people under Operation Pelican since 
it started on the morning of 10 May. The hashish ring under 
investigation is alleged to have brought 150 tons of hashish 
from Morocco to Spain over the last few years. The operation is 
being conducted in 14 provinces as well as abroad. (Madrid 
RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 10 May 94) 

</TEXT>

