<H3> <TI>   Cardenist Candidate Asserts Drug Traffickers Behind Colosio </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cardenist Candidate Asserts Drug Traffickers Behind Colosio </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Assassination 

<F P=102>   94WB0036C Mexico City EXCELSIOR in Spanish 21 Apr 94 pp 4-A, 
46-A </F>

<F P=103> 94WB0036C </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City EXCELSIOR </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by R. Rodriguez] </F>
  [Excerpts] Chilpancingo, Guerrero, 20 April--"Luis Donaldo 
Colosio Murrieta's assassination did not originate in any 
national conspiracy involving very powerful groups or 
politicians." This assertion was made here today by Rafael 
Aguilar Talamantes, candidate for the presidency of the republic 
from the Party of the Cardenist Front for National 
Reconstruction (PFCRN). 
  He added: "Colosio's sacrifice was due to regional interests 
of drug trafficking Mafias which, finding their financial income 
impaired, took revenge on President Carlos Salinas de Gortari by 
killing his favorite political son. They realized that they 
would be striking him where it hurt most." [passage omitted] 
  Rafael Aguilar Talamantes remarked that, during the Salinas 
de Gortari regime, a strenuous battle was waged (and is still 
being waged) throughout the national territory to take 
prosecutory action against the interests of the Mafias engaged 
in drug growing and trafficking. No such battle ever occurred 
during any other six-year term, he noted, adding that this meant 
that "those hurt would take revenge on someone whose death would 
grieve the president, and that person was, indisputably, Colosio 
Murrieta." 
  He commented: "By killing Colosio, they knew that they would 
deal a severe moral and political blow to his benefactor, his 
political father." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

