  [Excerpt] Hermosillo, Sonora, 20 April--A shipment of 
nearly a ton of cocaine was seized early this morning at the PGR 
[Attorney General's Office] checkpoint set up at Km 120 north of 
this town. The announcement was made by Miguel Angel Cortes 
Ibarra, the PGR's circuit representative. 
  The federal official added that these drugs were concealed 
under a load of pine logs arriving from the southern part of the 
country, and were bound for a site in the state's northern 
section. 
  The drugs were being transported on a gray Kenworth tractor 
trailer truck with Federal Public Service [SPF] plates 660-AT-1, 
hitched to a red flatbed carrying SPF plates 371-TXS. The 
information concerning the driver was not disclosed, so as to 
avoid interfering with the pertinent investigation [passage 
omitted] 

