<F P=101> VENEZUELA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Intelligence Service Dismantles Drug Trafficking Operation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Intelligence Service Dismantles Drug Trafficking Operation </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
`Rainbow' 

<F P=102>   PA1005204194 Maracaibo PANORAMA in Spanish 9 May 94 p 4-12 </F>
<F P=103> PA1005204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Maracaibo PANORAMA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Juan Carlos Guillen] </F>
  [Text] Deputy Julio Montoya has reported that the 
Directorate of Intelligence and Prevention Services dismantled 
Operation Rainbow in which drug traffickers were trying to 
export 300 tons of cocaine overseas. 
  "I have come to discuss and announce the discovery of a 
major 
drug-trafficking network whose primary hubs were the ports of 
Maracaibo, Puerto Cabello, and Punto Fijo," Montoya said. 
  Operation Rainbow used hollowed-out coconuts in which the 
drug--presumably cocaine--would be hidden. 
  [Guillen] How many kilograms would be exported that way? 
  [Montoya] Three hundred tons of the drug. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

