<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> LAOS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Over 2,000 Kg of Marijuana Destroyed in Vientiane </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Over 2,000 Kg of Marijuana Destroyed in Vientiane </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1405090194 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1405090194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Some 2,380 kilos of dry and raw marijuana seized in 
Vientiane Province were destroyed on 12 May by provincial 
narcotics control and suppression authorities in the presence of 
several officials from other services concerned in the province. 
The destroyed marijuana was discovered and seized by provincial 
economic police authorities in their search for marijuana 
plantations operated by certain opportunists in many localities 
in the province since mid-1993. The destroyed haul was valued at 
12.8 million kip [Lao currency]. Fifty-three marijuana planters, 
mostly residents of Kasi District, were reprimanded and fined by 
the local authorities concerned in accordance with the law. 

</TEXT>

