<F P=100> EAST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Than 120 Kg of Heroin Seized at Danube Bridge Checkpoint </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Than 120 Kg of Heroin Seized at Danube Bridge Checkpoint </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1205161894 Sofia BTA in English 1533 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1205161894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ruse, May 12 (BTA) -- More than 120 kg of 
heroin--refined, according to police sources, and unrefined, 
according to the prosecuting magistracy--have been seized at the 
Danube Bridge checkpoint in Ruse. The narcotic was distributed 
in about 250 packets and concealed under the bed on top the 
driver's cabin of a Fiat caravan which was leaving Bulgaria. 
The boy and the girl--both from Germany--travelling in the Fiat 
were arrested. This is the largest amount of heroin discovered 
at the Danube Bridge checkpoint so far. 

</TEXT>

