<H3> <TI>   Antidrug Efforts Figure `Highly' in Police Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Antidrug Efforts Figure `Highly' in Police Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Protocol   With France, Spain 

<F P=102> BR1605130394 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1915 GMT 13 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BR1605130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "France/Spain/Italy: Police </F>
Cooperation Protocol Signed"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 13 -- The commander general of 
Italy's Carabinieri force, General Luigi Federici, with a 
mandate from the ministry of the interior, Thursday [12 May] 
signed a protocol agreement with his counterparts from France 
and Spain so that the police departments from the three 
countries can work more closely together, an official communique 
from the Carabinieri's general command reported here this 
evening. 
  Patrice Maynial signed for the French national gendarmerie, 
while Ferran Cardenal De Alemany signed for the Spanish Civil 
Guard. 
  The three police forces agreed to step up their ties within 
the framework of international accords and national norms, with 
regard to training, recruitment, the organization of services, 
the exchange of information and experience, scientific data and 
techniques, and the acquisition of new technologies. 
  The battle against drugs will figure highly in their 
cooperative efforts, plus, in addition to their crime-fighting 
activities, the three institutions also will promote protection 
of the environment and of the artistic heritage of their 
countries. 

</TEXT>

