<F P=106> [Vadim Ogurtsov report: "Smuggler Arrested"] </F>
  [Text] The Federal Counterintelligence Service's Rostov 
Oblast Directorate Press Service has announced that a Turkmen 
citizen, wanted as one of the leaders of a criminal group 
involved in the illegal large-scale trafficking of drugs from 
Southeast Asia to Central Asia and Russia, has been arrested in 
Rostov-na-Donu as a result of operational-investigative measures 
conducted in conjunction with the personnel of Turkmenistan's 
National Security Committee [NSC]. Criminal proceedings have 
been instituted against the detainee under Article 72-2 of 
Turkmenistan's Criminal Code. The criminal was handed over to 
this state's NSC 12 May. 

