<H3> <TI>   Military Exercise Held To Practice Closing Tajik Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Exercise Held To Practice Closing Tajik Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205100794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0920 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Maynayev] </F>
  [Text] Bishkek May 12 TASS -- The largest military one-day 
exercise involving Kirgizian [Kyrgyz] Armed Forces, national 
guards, interior, security, and civil defense forces, began on 
Thursday in the south of the country. 
  The aim is to train how to close the border with Tajikistan 
which has become a transit place for illegal drugs from 
Afghanistan, according to the press service of Kirgizian 
President Askar Akayev who is inspecting the exercise. 

</TEXT>

