<H3> <TI>   Accused MP Resigns From Chat Thai Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Accused MP Resigns From Chat Thai Party </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2105093994 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2105093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Chat Thai Party has approved the resignation 
of Thanong Siriprichaphong, member of the House of 
Representatives from Nakhon Phanom, who is accused by the United 
States of being involved in the narcotics trade. Thanong's 
resignation from the party thus automatically terminated his 
membership in the House. 
  Speaking to reporters at Chat Thai Party's head office at 
noon today, Banhan Sinlapa-acha, leader of Chat Thai Party, said 
that the approval of Thanong Siriprichaphong's resignation was 
made on the recommendation of the fact-finding committee set up 
earlier by the party. However, as yet, Thanong Siriprichaphong 
is still considered innocent because the court has not yet ruled 
that he is guilty. Banhan said the drug charge against Thanong 
has caused severe damage to the country and its political 
institutions as well as to the Chat Thai Party. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

