First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The plan to strengthen public order in the 
country, including stricter observance of traffic regulations, 
will be enforced from 22 May using undercover inspectors. 
Brigadier-General Syfollahi, commander of the Law Enforcement 
Force, said this at a news conference today. [passage omitted] 
  Brig-Gen Seyfollahi also referred to the efforts of the Law 
Enforcement Force to fight smugglers in the past two months. He 
said: In that period a ship carrying contraband, bound for Iran 
from Dubai; a 10-[metric]tonne truck carrying technical 
equipment for smuggling [as heard]; 2,208,681 other contraband 
goods worth 12 billion rials; 2,533 boats; seven launches; and 
78 vehicles were seized and 2,061 smugglers were arrested in 
Bushehr, Hormozgan, and Chabahar areas in the second phase of 
the Fajr-3 exercises. 
  Asked about the discovery of narcotics, Brig-Gen Seyfollahi 
said that since the beginning of the year over 15 tonnes of 
assorted narcotics have been discovered. In that connection 
more than 1,400 smugglers and 2,000 addicts have been arrested. 

</TEXT>

