<H3> <TI>   Heroin, Opium Seizure in Khorasan Province Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Heroin, Opium Seizure in Khorasan Province Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805200494 Tehran IRNA in English 1830 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1805200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mashhad (Khorasan) May 18, IRNA -- Over the past 
week 806 kgs of opium and 3.5 kgs of heroin were seized from 
traffickers near the desert areas of this northeastern border 
province. 
  According to Colonel Sardar Hamid-Reza Musavi of the 
Khorasan 
law enforcement personnel, the latest drug haul was the result 
of the `saeqa' (lightning) operations staged simultaneously in 
23 security regions of the province. 
  Last year 130 clashes occurred with armed bandits which 
resulted in the death of 61 `death merchants' and arrest of 58 
others, he added. 
  Also during the same period 55 different weapons and 100 
grenades were seized from the traffickers. 

