<F P=102>   MB1705123194 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1157 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1705123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cape Town May 17 SAPA -- Police at Beaufort West in 
the Karoo have confiscated dagga [marijuana] with a street value 
of R[rand]7,500,000, SABC [South African Broadcasting 
Corporation] radio news reported on Tuesday. The consignment 
was apparently destined for the Cape Town market. This was the 
biggest dagga haul this year and the second biggest in the 
Western Cape in the past two years. A traffic officer stopped 
an unlicensed lorry and found 7,000 kg of dagga packed into 301 
bags. A 32-year-old Cape Town man was arrested and will appear 
in court soon. 

</TEXT>

