<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Swahili </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The government has launched a campaign to deal 
with drug traffickers, with effect from today, and has called on 
Tanzanians to expose all those involved in drug trafficking. 
Addressing Mlandizi residents in Kibaha District, the deputy 
prime minister and minister for home affairs, the Honorable 
Mrema, said that the government had resolved to launch the 
campaign when it realized that Tanzania had now been turned into 
a transit point for drugs. The Honorable Mrema stated that the 
government would reward those who expose drug traffickers. 
However, he did not specify the amount to be paid to those who 
would assist the government in arresting the traffickers. He 
pointed out that, after five or 10 years, Tanzania would have 
many mentally destabilized youth as a result of drug abuse. 
[passage omitted] 

