<F P=101> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bucharest Court Hears Defendants in Cocaine Smuggling Case </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bucharest Court Hears Defendants in Cocaine Smuggling Case </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1705064894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1814 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1705064894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 16/5/1994 -- The Bucharest 
Court heard in the 16 May public session a part of the 
defendants in the trial of the Dogmanov group standing charges 
of drug traffic, forgery and use of forgery and traffic of 
weapons and ammunition. The defendants, two of whom are 
Colombian citizens, explained how they got acquainted abroad and 
started the drug traffic connection. They managed as early as 
1990 to bring several consignments of drugs in Romania, using, 
among other things a marble table and 21 pictures. The last 
consignment, containing about 100 kg cocaine, was concealed in 
the pedestals of two statutes. The Romanian police managed to 
trace them and arrested the whole connection, led by Romanian 
Alexandru Sava Dogmanov. The defendants heard by the court 
today pleaded guilty of a part of the offenses. 

</TEXT>

