<H3> <TI>   Council of Ministers `Upgrades' National Antidrug Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council of Ministers `Upgrades' National Antidrug Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1805200694 Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY in English 1545 GMT 
18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1805200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nicosia, May 18 (CNA)--The Council of Ministers, 
headed by President Glavkos Kliridhis, decided Wednesday the 
upgrade of the national committee for the prevention of the 
trafficking and use of drugs. 
  This upgrade aims at the better flexibility of the national 
committee in taking and implementing its decisions, an official 
announcement said. 
  Moreover, a ministerial committee will function within the 
scope of the national committee, aimed at shaping the policy of 
the Council of Ministers, monitoring the implementation of the 
policy and coordinating the whole work of prevention. 
  The ministerial committee will be headed by the minister of 
health and include the ministers of justice and public order, 
education and culture, and labour and social insurance. The 
president of the Cyprus youth organisations will also be present. 
  In addition, three scientific committees will be set up with 
the participation of scientists from both the private and public 
sectors, to deal with research, prevention, treatment and 
rehabilitation. 

</TEXT>

