<F P=106> [Article signed UC: "Eight Kilos of Cocain Seized in </F>
Chiasso"] 
  [Text] Chiasso, 15 May (ATS/ANSA) -- Eight kilos of cocaine 
worth 7.2 million Swiss francs were seized during the night from 
Saturday [14 May] to Sunday [15 May] onboard the Zurich-Rome 
train at Chiasso station. The drugs were found inside the 
suitcase of a 28-year-old Polish national, who claimed he did 
not know what was inside the suitcase. According to the customs 
service, the cocaine came from Argentina and was bound for Rome. 
  On 24 March, 11 kg of cocaine from Argentina were seized. 
Three individuals, two Italian brothers and one Latin American 
national, were arrested in that seizure. 

