<F P=102>   TA2105104294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1510 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2105104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kocaeli, May 19 (A.A) -- Sixty-five kilo of heroin 
were seized in operations carried out by narcotics teams on 
Thursday in Kocaeli with a market value of 30 billion lira, it 
was reported. 
  Two people were detained in this connection. 
  A statement from Kocaeli Security Department said that 
narcotics teams acting on a tip-off searched a truck which was 
on its way to board a ferry in Derince, in Izmit Gulf. 
  65 kilos of heroin were found hidden in secret compartments 
of the truck. 
  The detainees said the heroin was given to them by a man of 
Iranian origin and made an agreement to carry it to Romania, 
where they would hand it back to him. 
  Police said they will start initiatives towards Romania for 
cooperation in finding the Iranian believed to be presently 
there. 

