<H3> <TI>   Cryogenic Payload To Measure Ozone Depletion Launched </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cryogenic Payload To Measure Ozone Depletion Launched </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1604160094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1604160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The indigenously developed cryogenic payload for 
measuring ozone depletion was successfully launched from 
National Scientific Payload Facility in Hyderabad today. Our 
Bangalore correspondent reports that with this, ISRO [Indian 
Space Research Organization] has become one among the very few 
countries in the world to develop and successfully employ this 
advanced cryogenic technique. Part of ISRO's geosphere program, 
the cryogenic payload will also measure the greenhouse warming 
substances in the atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

